elings of disappointment but also call for ethical gestures of empathy and reconciliation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAngolan literature (Portuguese)y20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aCuban literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847592940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438475929423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438475929/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles